				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{FE}}({\mathrm{\% }}) = \frac{{m\cdot n\cdot F}}{{I\cdot t}}\cdot 100{\mathrm{\% }},$$\end{document}where m is the number of moles of gas produced; n is the number of reaction electrons; F is the Faraday constant; I is the photocurrent; t is the reaction time.
